": \"my community\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1810}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All the LGBT folks, you guys brought me home that last hundred [meters].\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1884, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"you guys\", \"from\": 1832, \"to\": 1840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I could just feel the love and support.\\\"\", \"from\": 1885, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the love\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"support\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now Hiltz will be running for their community in the Olympics, and very much against the grain when one considers the retrograde approach that the transphobic World Athletics, the global governing body for track and field, has taken when it comes to trans participation.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2086, \"end\": 2101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6769655699182445e-30, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Hiltz\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"their community\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"the grain\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2021}, {\"ngram\": \"one\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"the retrograde approach\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2064}, {\"ngram\": \"the global governing body\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 2133, \"to\": 2138}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2148}, {\"ngram\": \"trans participation\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2196}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In March 2023, it issued newguidelinesthat, in essence, banned transgender women athletes from participating in World Athletics events: The group \\\"agreed to exclude male-to-female transgender athletes who have been through male puberty.\\\"\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2310, \"end\": 2325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6769655699182445e-30, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2206}, {\"ngram\": \"essence\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2252}, {\"ngram\": \"transgender women athletes\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2287}, {\"ngram\": \"The group\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2343}, {\"ngram\": \"male-to-female transgender athletes\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"male puberty\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics is headed by former Olympian and International Olympic Committee member Sebastian Coe, who emphasized the desire to assure \\\"the integrity of the female category in athletics\\\" andstated, \\\"We will be guided in this by the science around physical performance and male advantage which will inevitably develop over the coming years.\\\"\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2437, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6769655699182445e-30, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5897644079479905e-16, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2486, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2525, \"end\": 2538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the desire\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2565}, {\"ngram\": \"the integrity\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2590}, {\"ngram\": \"the female category\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2613}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2626}, {\"ngram\": \"the science\", \"from\": 2669, \"to\": 2680}, {\"ngram\": \"physical performance\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"male advantage\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2727}, {\"ngram\": \"the coming years\", \"from\": 2763, \"to\": 2779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Implicit in his official statement was a two-prong admission: (1) This policy targeted trans women, and (2) there is currently no scientific consensus-rooted in systematic, independent research-that justifies the exclusion of trans athletes.\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 3023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2869, \"end\": 2880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5452473630406425e-14, \"text\": \"trans women\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Implicit\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2790}, {\"ngram\": \"his official statement\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2816}, {\"ngram\": \"a two-prong admission\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2842}, {\"ngram\": \"This policy\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2859}, {\"ngram\": \"the exclusion\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 3004}, {\"ngram\": \"trans athletes\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3022}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's just a vibes thing.\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3048, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a vibes thing\", \"from\": 3034, \"to\": 3047}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What about the International Olympic Committee?\", \"from\": 3050, \"to\": 3097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3065, \"end\": 3096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Back in 2021, months after trans athleteLaurel Hubbardrepresented New Zealand in weightlifting-and the world kept on chugging along-the IOCissueda \\\"framework on fairness and non-discrimination on the basis of gender identity and sex variations\\\" that, on its surface, sounded promising.\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3383, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"trans\", \"from\": 3125, \"to\": 3130}, {\"ngram\": \"weightlifting\", \"from\": 3179, \"to\": 3192}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3197, \"to\": 3206}, {\"ngram\": \"the IOCissueda \\\"framework\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3255}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 3259, \"to\": 3267}, {\"ngram\": \"discrimination\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3290}, {\"ngram\": \"the basis\", \"from\": 3294, \"to\": 3303}, {\"ngram\": \"gender identity\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3322}, {\"ngram\": \"sex variations\", \"from\": 3327, \"to\": 3341}, {\"ngram\": \"its surface\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3363}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The framework appeared to be rooted in inclusion (\\\"Everyone, regardless of their gender identity, expression and/or sex variations should be able to participate in sport safely and without prejudice\\\"), nondiscrimination (\\\"Eligibility criteria should be established and implemented fairly and in a manner that does not systematically exclude athletes from competition based upon their gender identity, physical appearance and/or sex variations\\\"), and the assumption that no one was inherently advantaged by gender (\\\"No athlete should be precluded from competing or excluded from competition on the exclusive ground of an unverified, alleged or perceived unfair, competitive advantage due to their sex variations, physical appearance and/or transgender status\\\").\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 4144, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The framework\", \"from\": 3384, \"to\": 3397}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3432}, {\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 3435, \"to\": 3443}, {\"ngram\": \"their gender identity\", \"from\": 3459, \"to\": 3480}, {\"ngram\": \"expression\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3492}, {\"ngram\": \"sex variations\", \"from\": 3500, \"to\": 3514}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3548, \"to\": 3553}, {\"ngram\": \"prejudice\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3582}, {\"ngram\": \"Eligibility criteria\", \"from\": 3606, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"a manner\", \"from\": 3679, \"to\": 3687}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3725, \"to\": 3733}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 3739, \"to\": 3750}, {\"ngram\": \"their gender identity\", \"from\": 3762, \"to\": 3783}, {\"ngram\": \"physical appearance\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3804}, {\"ngram\": \"sex variations\", \"from\": 3812, \"to\": 3826}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 3854, \"to\": 3860}, {\"ngram\": \"gender\", \"from\": 3890, \"to\": 3896}, {\"ngram\": \"No athlete\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 3909}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 3962, \"to\": 3973}, {\"ngram\": \"the exclusive ground\", \"from\": 3977, \"to\": 3997}, {\"ngram\": \"an unverifie