d, LGBT, and undocumented.\\\"\", \"from\": 6115, \"to\": 6317, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 6123, \"to\": 6127}, {\"ngram\": \"a process\", \"from\": 6131, \"to\": 6140}, {\"ngram\": \"state power\", \"from\": 6162, \"to\": 6173}, {\"ngram\": \"all obstacles\", \"from\": 6187, \"to\": 6200}, {\"ngram\": \"the operation\", \"from\": 6204, \"to\": 6217}, {\"ngram\": \"racial capitalism\", \"from\": 6221, \"to\": 6238}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6250, \"to\": 6256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They added, \\\"In the United States, this is taking the form of eliminating legal protections for all marginalized people as well as the transformation of educational institutions to eradicate critical content, the maintenance of horrific border and immigration systems, and the prioritization of the needs of capital over climate change.\\\"\", \"from\": 6318, \"to\": 6655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6338, \"end\": 6351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998339477845377, \"rank\": 0.00016607979369548482, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Federal_government_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the form\", \"from\": 6368, \"to\": 6376}, {\"ngram\": \"legal protections\", \"from\": 6392, \"to\": 6409}, {\"ngram\": \"all marginalized people\", \"from\": 6414, \"to\": 6437}, {\"ngram\": \"the transformation\", \"from\": 6449, \"to\": 6467}, {\"ngram\": \"educational institutions\", \"from\": 6471, \"to\": 6495}, {\"ngram\": \"critical content\", \"from\": 6509, \"to\": 6525}, {\"ngram\": \"the maintenance\", \"from\": 6527, \"to\": 6542}, {\"ngram\": \"horrific border and immigration systems\", \"from\": 6546, \"to\": 6585}, {\"ngram\": \"the prioritization\", \"from\": 6591, \"to\": 6609}, {\"ngram\": \"the needs\", \"from\": 6613, \"to\": 6622}, {\"ngram\": \"capital\", \"from\": 6626, \"to\": 6633}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 6639, \"to\": 6653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This nexus of fascism, the Olympics, and anti-trans ideology recalls one of the darkest periods of Olympic history: when Nazis, notorious for their anti-queer persecution, convinced World Athletics (then called the International Amateur Athletic Federation) and the IOC to instigate sex-testing policies.\", \"from\": 6657, \"to\": 6961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6778, \"end\": 6783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_supremacy\", \"score\": 0.9139780731605559, \"rank\": 0.09411814956230737, \"text\": \"Nazis\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_supremacy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/White_supremacy\"}, {\"begin\": 6839, \"end\": 6854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6769655699182445e-30, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 6872, \"end\": 6913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Amateur Athletic Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 6923, \"end\": 6926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.307699576939538e-41, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This nexus\", \"from\": 6657, \"to\": 6667}, {\"ngram\": \"fascism\", \"from\": 6671, 